      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: document agent issue and PR routing",
        "body": "Closes #96712\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFresh coding agents can find `AGENTS.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, the issue forms, `CODEOWNERS`, and the PR template, but the issue/PR/contact routing is spread across those files. That makes it easy for a first-time agent to file the wrong issue shape, omit required evidence, skip the PR template, or guess who to tag.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdds a compact issue/PR/contact routing map to `CONTRIBUTING.md`, a stricter fresh-agent checklist to the `AGENTS.md` GitHub/PR section, and short front-door links in the README Community section. The change only documents existing process primitives: issue forms, blank-issue policy, PR body sections, evidence expectations, Discord/support routing, security routing, maintainer areas, and `CODEOWNERS`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAgent-authored and AI-assisted contributions get a deterministic path from the README and repo-root process docs for filing bugs, docs bugs, feature requests, support questions, security reports, and PRs. Maintainers should see fewer process-shape mistakes because agents are told where to look, what evidence to include, and when not to guess tags or contacts.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm docs:list` (passed; command hydrated dependencies before listing docs)\n- `git diff --check`\n- `git ls-files CODEOWNERS .github/CODEOWNERS` (returns `.github/CODEOWNERS`)\n- `git status -sb` showed only the intended docs files changed before each commit\n",
